<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{deshou@EM{{ni}}}} indicates that something regrettably has happened, although things could have turned out differently.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{hokano@KJ{{person}}gayattara,motto@KJ{{early}}kudekitadeshou@EM{{ni}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It could have been finished much sooner had someone else done it.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@HI{{darou}} can be used instead of @HI{{deshou}}.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{mou@KJ{{few}}shi@KJ{{wait}}tteitara,@KJ{{rain}}gayandarou@EM{{ni}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      If we had waited a little longer the rain might have stopped.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
If @HI{{deshou@EM{{ni}}}} follows a conditional clause and a non-past verb or adjective, then this is
a supposition that is counter to the current situation. If the subject of the conditional clause is the
first person, the whole sentence expresses regret. Otherwise it expresses the speaker's sympathy for
that subject.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{fly^going^mechanism}}:hikouki}}de@KJ{{going}}keba@FG{{@KJ{{simplicity^simple}}:kantan'}}ni@KJ{{going}}keru@FG{{@KJ{{location}}:tokoro}}deshouni.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      If you go by place, you could easily get there.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
If @HI{{deshou@EM{{ni}}}} follows a conditional clause and a past verb or adjective, then this is 
a supposition that is counter to the past situation. If the subject of the conditional clause is the
first person, the whole sentence expresses regret. Otherwise it expresses the speaker's sympathy for
that subject.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{me}}niii@KJ{{attend^matter}}gaattara@FG{{@KJ{{beauty^wisdom^child}}:michiko}}santo@KJ{{tie^marriage^exit^come}}tadarouni.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      If I had had a good job I could have married Michiko.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
If there is no conditional clause at all, then the entire sentence expresses sympathy.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{old*man^person}}:roujin'}}ga@KJ{{one^person}}de@FG{{@KJ{{livelihood}}:ku}}rasunohasazo@FG{{@KJ{{loneliness}}:sabi}}shiideshou@EM{{ni}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It must be lonely for an old man to live alone.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
@HI{{@EM{{ni}}}} often follows @HI{{darou}}, @HI{{deshou}} and @V{{}}@HI{{tarou}}.
</p>

<p>
